A Tsukuba Express train driver fell asleep at the wheel and was reported by a
customer who used his cell phone to film the driver's slumber. While many
bloggers expressed relief that this didn't cause an accident, ruhiginoue
wonders [why the line needs drivers](http://ruhiginoue.exblog.jp/11816824/)
[ja] when it's equipped with an automatic train operation system
([ATO](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automatic_train_operation)) and blogger
a205750un asks if there's something in the [electromagnetic rays that induces
sleepiness](http://blog.goo.ne.jp/a205750un/e/f987c11329e99dcd2308c852aeb498aa)
[ja].

